This article is a presidential proclamation by Barack Obama on the anniversary of the Americans with Disabilities Act (ADA). The proclamation recognizes the efforts of individuals with disabilities who fought against discrimination and emphasizes the need to continue tearing down barriers and ensuring equal rights and opportunities for all Americans. The ADA promises equal access and equal opportunity, securing each person's right to an independent life and allowing the country and economy to benefit from the talents and contributions of disabled individuals. The proclamation also highlights ongoing efforts to fulfill the promise of the ADA, such as increasing the number of homes integrated into communities for persons with disabilities and banning insurance companies from discriminating based on pre-existing conditions. The proclamation encourages Americans to celebrate the 24th anniversary of the ADA and the contributions of individuals with disabilities.